main_body:
The intervention agencies of Belgium, the Czech Republic, Ireland, Italy, Hungary, Slovakia and Sweden listed in Annex I shall offer for sale a total quantity of 345 539 tonnes of sugar by standing invitation to tender for export to all destinations, excluding the following:
(a) third countries: Andorra, Liechtenstein, the Holy See (Vatican City State), Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Montenegro, Albania, the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia, and Serbia, as well as Kosovo under UNSC Resolution 1244/99;
(b) territories of EU Member States not forming part of the customs territory of the Community: the Faeroe Islands, Greenland, Heligoland, Ceuta, Melilla, the communes of Livigno and Campione d'Italia, and the areas of the Republic of Cyprus in which the Government of the Republic of Cyprus does not exercise effective control;
(c) European territories for whose external relations a Member State is responsible not forming part of the customs territory of the Community: Gibraltar.
The maximum quantities involved per Member State are set out in Annex I.
The tendering procedure shall determine the selling price.
